    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they use different frameworks, but in a real debate, you usually have to commit to a hierarchy of values. if you had to pick which one is more fundamental to a stable society, wouldn't a functioning state with secure borders be the prerequisite for even being able to provide asylum in the first place? it feels like the security argument is more logically foundational.",
